{
  "texts": [
    "(3) additional model evaluation based on eye-tracking metrics that capture the interaction between text and readers.",
    "Reading comprehension involves multiple cognitive processes (Kintsch, 1998), from word and sentence processing to integrating the text with a reader's prior knowledge (Kintsch, 1994; McNamara and Magliano, 2009).",
    "These processes unfold chronologically, but they extend beyond simple leftto-right reading, as eye movements have non-linear patterns of word fixation and skipping (Engbert et al., 2004).",
    "Accurately modeling both spatial and temporal aspects of eye movements is thus essential to understand reading behavior.",
    "Empirical evidence is plentiful for the link between specific eye movement features (fixation duration, location, etc.)"
  ]
}